9.7.19  11:20 pm   At one point you mentioned shifting your sleep schedule slightly later each day. Did you know that this is considered a sleeping disorder?

      https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-24-hour_sleep%E2%80%93wake_disorder

Supposedly it is caused because the brain does not react normally to the light cues that normally maintain people's circadian rhythms.

      I'm not diagnosing you with this, I was just curious if you were aware of it. If you actually had this disorder it would mean you would be pretty incapable of maintaining a normal sleep schedule without significant insomnia.
